# Commit Message Rules for Restrict Language

# FORMAT:
# <type>: <subject> (max 50 chars)
#
# <body> (optional, wrap at 72 chars)
#
# <footer> (optional)

# TYPES:
# - feat: New feature
# - fix: Bug fix
# - docs: Documentation only
# - style: Formatting, no code change
# - refactor: Code restructuring
# - test: Adding tests
# - chore: Maintenance

# RULES:
# 1. NO emoji in commit messages
# 2. NO "Generated with Claude" or similar signatures
# 3. NO Co-Authored-By for AI tools
# 4. Keep subject line under 50 characters
# 5. Use imperative mood ("Add" not "Added")
# 6. No period at end of subject line
# 7. Separate subject from body with blank line
# 8. Wrap body at 72 characters
# 9. Explain what and why, not how

# EXAMPLES:
# Good:
#   fix: Restore WebAssembly code generation pipeline
#
#   All 8 WAT generation tests were failing due to parser not handling
#   function declarations correctly. Fixed by supporting both complex
#   and simple syntax styles.
#
# Bad:
#   Fixed the bug in the code generator 🤖
#   Co-Authored-By: Claude